latestIgtvVideos.title: Paruppu Vadai (masala Vada )
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
You can also Call it Indian Falafel or Keere Vadai 

This is a South Indian tea time snack made with chana dal, tur Dal, spices, onions & herbs. It is also a street food & most commonly served at Snack centers all across south india as a evening snack with a chutney. 

You can Deep fry them, Bake them or Air fry them ..... 

Ingredients for the Dal Vada 

* Tur Dal : 1/2 cup 
* Chanda dal : 1/2 cup 
* Red chillies : 5 to 6 (deseeded) 
* Onion : 1/2 cup 
* Amaranth (leafy vegetable) : 1 cup 
* Coriander : 1/4 cup 
* Green chilly : 1 tbsp 
* Jeera : 2 tsp 
* Pepper powder : 2 tsp 
* Ginger : 1 tbsp 
* Salt to Taste 
* Oil for frying 
* Curry leaves : 1 tbsp 

You have to soak Both dals with red chilly for 1 Hr, don’t add water while grinding (otherwise it will absorb lot of oil) 

You can also add 1/2 rice to your recipe or add rice flour while mixing everything ....
The vadas will be crispier.... 

Do try the recipe and share pictures ❤️

Bharwan Bhindi 🫶🏻

One recipe that can never go wrong ✨ simple, comforting and just so good that you’ll make it on repeat

3 Must-Try South Indian Street Food Delights from the Streets of Mumbai!🌴🍛

Crispy, spicy & bursting with flavour – straight from the stalls to your plate!

* Jini Dosa
* Spot Idli 
* Matka Dosa 

Gini Dosa 

Recipe:
Ingredients (makes 2 dosas) 
* Dosa batter 1 cup 
* Butter 1/4 cup
* Cheese 1/2 cup
* Cabbage 1/4 cup
* Onions 1/4 cup
* Tomatoes 1/4 cup
* Green capsicum 1/4 cup
* Grated carrots 1/4 cup
* Spring onions 2 tbsp
* Schezwan sauce 1/4 cup
* Red chilli sauce 1/4 cup
* Tomato ketchup 1/4 cup
* Chaat masala pinch (optional) 
* Red chilli powder pinch (optional) 

Serve with Green chutney, ketchup or coconut chutney 

Spot Idli 

INGREDIENTS 
* Idli batter 1 cup
* Onions 1/2 cup
* Tomatoes 1/2 cup
* Ghee 1/4 cup
* Garlic 2 tsp
* Mustard 1 tsp
* Urad dal 2 tsp
* Curry leaves 2 tsp
* Asafoetida pinch
* Turmeric pinch
* Red chilli powder 1 tbsp
* Sambar masala 2 tsp
* Salt to taste 
* Coriander 1 tbsp 
* Green chillies 2 tsp
* Banana leaf 

Method 
* Make onion tomato vegetable with ghee basic masalas and sambar masala 
* On a tava , add ghee place banana leaf, place the sabji, pour idli batter sprinkle coriander, cover and cook till Idli is steamed 
* Once cooked place another banana leaf and cook on other side 
* Serve with chutney and sambar
